com.github.theholywaffle.teamspeak3.api.wrapper

Class ServerQueryInfo

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.theholywaffle.teamspeak3.api.wrapper.Wrapper
      • com.github.theholywaffle.teamspeak3.api.wrapper.ServerQueryInfo

  • public class ServerQueryInfo
extends Wrapper
    A class containing information about a server query, returned by the API methods TS3Api.whoAmI() and TS3ApiAsync.whoAmI().

    • Method Detail

      • getChannelId

        public int getChannelId()
        Gets the ID of the channel the server query is currently in.
        Returns:
        the ID of the current channel

      • getDatabaseId

        public int getDatabaseId()
        Gets the ID of the server query in the database.

        In case this server query account was created by a client, its database ID will be identical to the client's database ID.

        Returns:
        the server query's database ID

      • getId

        public int getId()
        Gets the client ID of the server query.
        Returns:
        the server query's client ID

      • getLoginName

        public String getLoginName()
        Gets the username that was used when logging the query in (using a username-password combination).

        This username was set when creating the server query login and doesn't have to be related to the client who created the server query login.
        In case a server query is not logged in yet, this method will return an empty string.

        Returns:
        the username used when logging this query in
        See Also:
        TS3Api#login(username, password) - logging in server queries

      • getNickname

        public String getNickname()
        Gets the nickname currently used by the server query. Unless explicitly set, the nickname will be formatted like 
        username from ip:port

        Nicknames are only assigned after a virtual server has been selected. Until then, this method will return an empty string.

        Returns:
        the current nickname of the server query

      • getOriginServerId

        public int getOriginServerId()
        Gets the ID of the virtual server on which the server query login was created.

        This method will return 0 (the ID of the template server) if a server query is not logged in or using the serveradmin login.

        Returns:
        the ID of the virtual server this server query belongs to

      • getUniqueIdentifier

        public String getUniqueIdentifier()
        Gets the unique identifier of the server query.

        In case this server query account was created by a client, its unique ID will be identical to the client's unique ID.

        Returns:
        the server query's unique ID

      • getVirtualServerId

        public int getVirtualServerId()
        Gets the ID of the currently selected virtual server.

        If used on a non-commercial TeamSpeak instance which can only host 1 virtual server, this ID will always be 1.
        If no virtual server has been selected yet, this method will return 0.

        Returns:
        the ID of the current virtual server or 0 if none is selected

      • getVirtualServerPort

        public int getVirtualServerPort()
        Gets the port used by the currently selected virtual server.

        If no virtual server has been selected yet, this method will return 0.

        Returns:
        the port used by the current virtual server or 0 if none is selected

      • getVirtualServerStatus

        public VirtualServerStatus getVirtualServerStatus()
        Gets the status of the currently selected virtual server.

        If no virtual server has been selected yet, this method will return VirtualServerStatus.UNKNOWN.

        Returns:
        the status of the current virtual server

      • getVirtualServerUniqueIdentifier

        public String getVirtualServerUniqueIdentifier()
        Gets the unique identifier of the currently selected virtual server.

        If no virtual server has been selected yet, this method will return an empty string.

        Returns:
        the unique ID of the current virtual server
